Using the corrplot

Libraries and data import

library(readxl) # read excel data
library(corrplot) # make correlation matrices

# just to make sure everything is in the right type
RA_norm <- read_excel("RA_norm.xlsx", col_types = c("date", 
    "numeric", "numeric", "numeric", "numeric", 
    "numeric", "numeric", "numeric", "numeric", 
    "numeric", "numeric", "numeric", "numeric", 
    "numeric", "numeric", "numeric"))
TJQ_norm <- read_excel("TJQ_norm.xlsx", col_types = c("date", 
    "numeric", "numeric", "numeric", "numeric", 
    "numeric", "numeric", "numeric", "numeric", 
    "numeric", "numeric", "numeric", "numeric", 
    "numeric", "numeric", "numeric", "numeric", 
    "numeric"))

Correlation claculation and Plots

Rodoanel Tunnel

M <- cor(RA_norm[,-1], use = "pairwise.complete.obs") # calc correlation w/o date column (col #1) and NA's
res <- cor.mtest(RA_norm[,-1], use = "pairwise.complete.obs", conf.level = .95)
# pdf(file = "RT_matrix.pdf", #
#     width = 10,             # Add to save PDF
#     height = 10)            #
corrplot.mixed(M,
               upper = "ellipse",
               order = "hclust", # do the organization by clusterization
               p.mat = res$p)

# dev.off()                   # Add to save PDF

Janio Quadros Tunnel

M <- cor(TJQ_norm[,-1], use = "pairwise.complete.obs") # calc correlation w/o date column (col #1) and NA's

PCA

library(tidyverse)
library(psych)
PCA <- RA_norm %>%
  select(NO, NO2, SO2, CO2, CO) %>% # just gases
  # select(NOx, NO, NO2, SO2, CO2, CO) %>% # just gases + NOx
  # select(NOx, NO, NO2, SO2, CO2, CO, Dfraction, LDV, HDV, EF_NOx, EF_NO, EF_NO2, EF_SO2, EF_CO2, EF_CO) %>% # 
  principal(nfactors = 5, rotate = 'varimax')
